STM32CubeMP2
###########

Origin:
   ST Microelectronics
   https://github.com/STMicroelectronics/STM32CubeMP2

Status:
   version v1.3.0

Purpose:
   ST Microelectronics official MCU package for STM32MP2 series.

Description:
   This package is an extract of official STM32CubeMP2 package written by ST Microelectronics.
   It is composed of STM32Cube hardware abstraction layer (HAL) and low layer (LL) plus a set
   of CMSIS headers files, one for each SoC in STM32MP2 series.

Dependencies:
    None.

URL:
   https://github.com/STMicroelectronics/STM32CubeMP2

Commit:
   38732d24f8928af2dbcd9491f92390efbaec78d6

Maintained-by:
   External

License:
   BSD-3-Clause

License Link:
   https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause

Patch List:
   *Changes from official delivery:
    -dos2unix applied
    -Trailing white spaces removed

   *Provision to enable hal & ll asserts added
    -Added stm32cube/stm32mp2xx/drivers/include/stm32_assert.h
    -Removed unused stm32cube/stm32mp2xx/drivers/include/stm32_assert_template.h

   *Fix to remove PAGESIZE definition which conflicts with POSIX
    Impacted files:
     drivers/include/Legacy/stm32_hal_legacy.h

   *Disable HAL LVDS module disabled
    Don't define HAL_LVDS_MODULE_ENABLED as LVDS HAL is not available yet.
    Impacted files:
      drivers/include/stm32mp2xx_hal_conf.h

   *Don't define USE_FULL_ASSERT by default
    Match behavior of other series by leaving USE_FULL_ASSERT undefined
    in the HAL configuration file. It can still be enabled using the
    Kconfig option CONFIG_USE_STM32_ASSERT, as on other series.
    Impacted files:
     drivers/include/stm32mp2xx_hal_conf.h

   *Add support for I2C8 clock configuration
    Allow retrieving the clock configuration of the I2C8 peripheral.
    Impacted files:
     drivers/src/stm32mp2xx_ll_rcc.c

   *Allow usage of HAL_DCMIPP_PIPE_SetConfig when DCMIPP is in READY state
     Allow performing PIPE configuration when the DCMIPP device is not only
     in RESET and ERROR states but also in READY state. This allow to
     reconfigure a DCMIPP pipe between 2 use-cases without having to
     call HAL_DCMIPP_DeInit / HAL_DCMIPP_Init.
     Impacted files:
      drivers/src/stm32mp2xx_hal_dcmipp.c
     Internal reference: 215688

   *ethernet: Fix ETH_DMA_XXX definitions
     On the Ethernet peripheral, there are two DMA channels.
     As a consequence, the ETH_DMACSR_XXX definitions do not exist and
     should be replaced by ETH_DMAC0SR_CDE and ETH_DMAC1SR_CDE.
     The workaround is to replace ETH_DMACSR_XXX with ETH_DMAC0SR_XXX.
     Impacted files:
      drivers/include/stm32mp2xx_hal_eth.h
     Internal reference: 220075

   See release_note.html from STM32Cube
